and expressed his hope that the festival would inspire everyone to work towards achieving prosperity by strengthening the Constitution and promoting national unity, social goodwill, and harmony.\n\nDescribing Nepal as a multilingual and multicultural nation with diverse and unique natural features, he remarked, \u201cOur civilization, religions, culture, festivals, and lifestyle all reflect our rich history and our present.\u201d\n\nHe also reminded everyone that the federal democratic republic established by Nepal\u2019s Constitution is a source of pride for all Nepali citizens.\n\nIndra Jatra, a festival dedicated to the God Indra, the deity of rain and good harvest, has a historical significance, particularly among the Newar community in the Kathmandu Valley.","title":"PM Dahal calls for making social justice and good governance national priorities","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2023/28/320107/","video":[]}
